ndustries over the last 30 years; they have an idea of what a revolutionary technology can do to static incumbents. So, to stay ahead of change, banks have been proactive in setting up R\u0026D labs, building test centers and establishing partnerships with blockchain developers to fully understand […]","thumbnail":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/blockchain.jpg","images":{"id":29018,"alt":"","mime":"image/jpeg","images":{"source":"","credit":"","creditUrl":"","captionUrl":"","url":"","desktop":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/blockchain-220x143.jpg","width":220,"height":143},"mobile":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/blockchain-286x190.jpg","width":286,"height":190},"mobile@2x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/blockchain-572x360.jpg","width":572,"height":360},"mobile@3x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/blockchain-858x570.jpg","width":858,"height":570},"full":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/blockchain.jpg","width":1000,"height":667}},"type":"image"},"guideSlug":"blockchain-101","active":false},{"title":"What is a Distributed Ledger?","slug":"what-is-a-distributed-ledger","excerpt":"Ledgers, the foundation of accounting, are as ancient as writing and money. Their medium has been clay, wooden tally sticks (that were a fire hazard), stone, papyrus and paper. Once computers became normalized in the 1980s and ’90s, paper records were digitized, often by manual data entry. These early digital ledgers mimicked the cataloguing and accounting […]","thumbnail":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.08.05-PM.png","images":{"id":544084,"alt":"","mime":"image/png","images":{"source":"","credit":"","creditUrl":"","captionUrl":"","url":"","desktop":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.08.05-PM-220x143.png","width":220,"height":143},"mobile":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.08.05-PM-286x190.png","width":286,"height":190},"mobile@2x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.08.05-PM-572x360.png","width":572,"height":360},"mobile@3x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.08.05-PM-858x570.png","width":858,"height":570},"full":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.08.05-PM.png","width":2170,"height":1072}},"type":"image"},"guideSlug":"blockchain-101","active":false},{"title":"Why Use a Blockchain?","slug":"why-use-a-blockchain","excerpt":"As the implications of the invention of have become understood, a certain hype has sprung up around blockchain technology. This is, perhaps, because it is so easy to imagine high-level use cases. But, the technology has also been closely examined: millions of dollars have been spent researching blockchain technology over the past few years, and […]","thumbnail":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.05.11-PM.png","images":{"id":544083,"alt":"","mime":"image/png","images":{"source":"Blockchain technology offers new tools for authentication and authorization in the digital world that preclude the need for many centralized administrators. ","credit":"","creditUrl":"","captionUrl":"","url":"","desktop":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.05.11-PM-220x143.png","width":220,"height":143},"mobile":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.05.11-PM-286x190.png","width":286,"height":190},"mobile@2x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Screen-Shot-2020-11-12-at-1.05.11-PM-572x360.png","width":572,"height":360},"mobile@3x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploa