acherous passes in any technological revolution. Some people in the blockchain industry have pointed out that blockchain has become overhyped, when, in reality, the technology has limitations and is inappropriate for many digital interactions. But through research and development, success and failure, and trial and error, we’ve learned the current issues and limitations of blockchains. […]","thumbnail":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/shutterstock_777275785.jpg","images":{"id":432320,"alt":"","mime":"image/jpeg","images":{"source":"","credit":"","creditUrl":"","captionUrl":"","url":"","desktop":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/shutterstock_777275785-220x143.jpg","width":220,"height":143},"mobile":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/shutterstock_777275785-286x190.jpg","width":286,"height":190},"mobile@2x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/shutterstock_777275785-572x360.jpg","width":572,"height":360},"mobile@3x":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/shutterstock_777275785-858x570.jpg","width":858,"height":570},"full":{"src":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/shutterstock_777275785.jpg","width":1200,"height":764}},"type":"image"},"guideSlug":"blockchain-101","active":false},{"title":"Hard Fork vs Soft Fork","slug":"hard-fork-vs-soft-fork","excerpt":"Last updated: 16 March, 2018 Forks, or the threat of them, seem to be an established feature of the cryptocurrency landscape. But what are they? Why are they such a big deal? And what is the difference between a hard fork and a soft fork? A “fork,” in programming terms, is an open-source code modification. […]","thumbnail":"https://static.coindesk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/shutterstock_752784025-scaled.jpg","images":{"id":296767,"alt":"https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/golden-bitcoin-silver-forks-752784025?src=_SOSLztdlHKkTgmiUDuv-g-2-30","mime":"image/jpeg","